================================================================================
Self-hosted model weights — Apache-2.0 (Ministral 3 + Magistral Small 24B)
================================================================================

The DEFAULT self-hosted chat model (modelServer.model =
ministral-3:3b-instruct-2512-q4_K_M, Mistral AI "Ministral 3" 3B) is licensed
under APACHE-2.0 — an OSI-permissive license. The weights are pulled at runtime
by the Ollama engine and are NOT redistributed as part of this product (see
THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES.md). The self-hosted default is therefore Apache-clean.

The self-hosted SOVEREIGN REASONING model (modelServer.reasoning, registered
with LiteLLM as sovereign-reasoning) is Mistral AI "Magistral Small 24B"
(Magistral-Small-2506-Q4_K_M.gguf), also licensed under APACHE-2.0. It is served
by the llama.cpp llama-server engine (MIT); the GGUF weights are provided/mounted
at runtime on the host and are NOT redistributed as part of this product. The
fast/fallback reasoning route (sovereign-reasoning-fast) is the managed STACKIT
API and ships no weights.

